#Text=The Memphis Grizzlies ( 45 - 18 ) defeated the Chicago Bulls ( 39 - 26 ) 101 - 91 on Monday at the United Center in Chicago .
#Text=While they were up just two points at the break , the Grizzlies used a strong second half , where they out - scored the Bulls 60 - 52 , to steal a road win in Chicago .
#Text=The Grizzlies were the superior shooters in this one , going 50 percent from the field , while the Bulls went just 44 percent .
#Text=What also made a big difference was turnovers though , as the Grizzlies forced the Bulls into 17 , while committing just 11 of their own .
#Text=The Grizzlies ' frontcourt was dominant in this matchup , out - scoring the Bulls ' frontcourt 68 - 21 .
#Text=Marc Gasol led the way , scoring a game - high of 23 points ( 10 - 16 FG , 3 - 3 FT ) , to go along with four rebounds and two blocked shots .
#Text=After struggling to just eight points against the Pelicans on Saturday , it was good to see one of the league 's best centers get back on track .
#Text=He 's now averaging 18 points and eight rebounds on the year .
#Text=Helping out Gasol was Zach Randolph , who nearly posted a double - double with 16 points ( 7 - 12 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 2 - 3 FT ) and nine rebounds in 30 minutes .

#Text=Like Gasol , he struggled against the Pelicans on Saturday , finishing that game with only seven points , so he was able to get things turned around as well and help Marc Gasol take down his brother Pau .
#Text=Jeff Green was dialed in with his shot , going 7 - for - 11 from the field and 3 - for - 4 from the three - point line to score 19 points , while adding seven rebounds as well .
#Text=He 's put in two impressive performances in a row , combining for 39 points and 13 rebounds over his last two .
#Text=Not only did those three do it on offense , but they also were able to do it defensively and limit the Bulls ' best player in Pau Gasol .
#Text=Pau Gasol finished with just 13 points ( 6 - 14 FG , 1 - 1 FT ) and 11 rebounds in 31 minutes .
#Text=While he did record a double - double , he needed to do even more , with the likes of Derrick Rose , Jimmy Butler and Taj Gibson all sitting out with injuries .
#Text=While the Bulls ' frontcourt did n't have much success , their backcourt is what kept them close .
#Text=Starting at shooting guard , Tony Snell posted a team - high of 21 points ( 7 - 13 FG , 4 - 7 3Pt , 3 - 4 FT ) , while adding two steals .
#Text=In just his fifteenth start of the year , he was able to post double - digit points after failing to do so in his previous three games .
#Text=Over his last three games he had combined for just 12 points , including going scoreless on Sunday against the Spurs , so we 'll see if that helps rebuild his confidence moving forward .
#Text=Aaron Brooks also got into the action with 15 points ( 6 - 14 FG , 1 - 3 3Pt , 2 - 2 FT ) of his own , to go along with four rebounds and four assists .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Nikola Mirotic double - doubled with 18 points ( 6 - 13 FG , 2 - 3 3Pt , 4 - 5 FT ) and 12 rebounds .
#Text=He 's on a very strong stretch of six games , where he 's averaging an impressive 21 points per game .
#Text=The Grizzlies ' next game will be on the road against the Boston Celtics on Wednesday , while the Bulls will travel to Philadelphia to play the Sixers on Wednesday .
